<emphasis bold="true" box="[1037,1166,1737,1761]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Synon. nov.</emphasis>
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1503,2027]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,758]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,257,1768,1794]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Note</emphasis>
:—Historically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[449,538,1769,1794]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[449,538,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Araujia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1838" authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1838" box="[604,715,1769,1794]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[604,715,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Morrenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been considered closely related genera but treated as distinct based on subtle differences such as the thickness and consistency of style-head and the corolla shape (
<emphasis box="[161,205,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">e.g.</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Goyder, D. J." box="[221,384,1846,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" pagination="713 - 721" refId="ref4840" refString="Goyder, D. J. (2003) A synopsis of Morrenia Lindl. (Apocynaceae subfam. Asclepiadoideae). Kew Bulletin 58: 713 - 721." type="journal article" year="2003">Goyder 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Goyder, D. J." box="[398,464,1846,1872]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" pagination="415 - 451" refId="ref4870" refString="Goyder, D. J. (2004) An amplified concept of Philibertia Kunth (Apocynaceae: Asclepiadoideae), with a synopsis of the genus. Kew Bulletin 59: 415 - 451." type="journal article" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
). A hyaline appendage on the corpusculum was also used to recognise 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[1336,1428,1847,1872]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1336,1428,1847,1872]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Araujia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, similar appendages are found in other genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[910,1078,1885,1911]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Oxypetalinae">Oxypetalinae</taxonomicName>
—for instance, 
<taxonomicName authority="Martius" authorityName="Martius" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Oxypetalum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="appendiculatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Oxypetalum appendiculatum</emphasis>
Martius
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[445,468,1924,1949]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">in</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Zuccarini, J. G." box="[475,839,1924,1950]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" pagination="25 - 55" refId="ref5816" refString="Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Zuccarini, J. G. (1824) Nova Genera et Species Plantarum, vol. 1, part 3. Lindauer, Munich, pp. 37 - 80, t. 25 - 55." type="book chapter" year="1824">Martius &amp; Zuccarini (1824: 48</bibRefCitation>
; t. 30)—and, on the other hand, this character state is not present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Schlechter (1895: 449)" authorityName="Schlechter" authorityPageNumber="449" authorityYear="1895" box="[349,766,1962,1988]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plumosa">
<emphasis box="[349,483,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">A. plumosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schlechter, R." box="[491,766,1962,1988]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" pagination="449 - 454" refId="ref6298" refString="Schlechter, R. (1895) Asclepiadaceae Kuntzeanae. Oesterreichische Botanische Zeitschrift 45: 449 - 454." type="journal article" year="1895">Schlechter (1895: 449)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Curiously, the latter species shares other attributes with species of 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1838" authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1838" box="[276,388,2001,2026]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[276,388,2001,2026]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="10">Morrenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as the fimbriate anther appendage and contorted anther wings (
<bibRefCitation author="Goyder, D. J." box="[1211,1369,2001,2027]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" pagination="713 - 721" refId="ref4840" refString="Goyder, D. J. (2003) A synopsis of Morrenia Lindl. (Apocynaceae subfam. Asclepiadoideae). Kew Bulletin 58: 713 - 721." type="journal article" year="2003">Goyder 2003</bibRefCitation>
) and, phylogenetically, it is more closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Hooker &amp; Arnott" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[685,817,152,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="odorata">
<emphasis box="[685,817,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">M. odorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[912,1057,152,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sericifera">
<emphasis box="[912,1057,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">A. sericifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a relationship highly supported based on plastid data (
<bibRefCitation author="Liede-Schumann, S. &amp; Rapini, A. &amp; Goyder, D. J. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[419,765,190,216]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" pagination="183 - 194" refId="ref5397" refString="Liede-Schumann, S., Rapini, A., Goyder, D. J. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2005) Phylogenetics of the New World subtribes of Asclepiadeae (Apocynaceae - Asclepiadoideae): Metastelmatinae, Oxypetalinae, and Gonolobinae. Systematic Botany 30: 183 - 194." type="journal article" year="2005">
Liede-Schumann 
<emphasis box="[632,693,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[787,878,191,216]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[787,878,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Araujia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1838" authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1838" box="[937,1050,191,216]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[937,1050,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Morrenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are small genera (with four and eight accepted species, respectively), they are difficult to distinguish as currently defined, and the recognition of 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1838" authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1838" box="[185,301,268,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[185,301,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Morrenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[397,490,268,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[397,490,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Araujia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
paraphyletic. The synonymisation of 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1838" authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1838" box="[964,1080,268,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[964,1080,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Morrenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[1168,1261,268,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1168,1261,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Araujia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will certainly provide a more stable classification, based on a monophyletic, easily recognisable group of reasonable size and geographic integrity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,758]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
<taxonomicName authority="C.F.P.Martius &amp; Zuccarini, 1824" authorityName="C.F.P.Martius &amp; Zuccarini" authorityYear="1824" box="[198,341,384,409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Physianthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[198,341,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Physianthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="E.Fournier, 1885" authorityName="Fournier" authorityYear="1885" box="[410,506,384,409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Lagenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[410,506,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Lagenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been treated in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[1006,1095,384,409]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1006,1095,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Araujia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
since 
<bibRefCitation author="Decaisne, J." box="[1182,1380,384,410]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" pagination="490 - 665" refId="ref4615" refString="Decaisne, J. (1844) Asclepiadaceae. In: Candolle, A. L. P. P. (ed.), Prodromus Systematis Naturalis Regni Vegetabilis, vol. 8. Treuttel &amp; Wurtz, Paris, pp. 490 - 665." type="book chapter" year="1844">Decaisne (1844)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Schumann, K. M." box="[151,363,422,448]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" pagination="189 - 306" refId="ref6430" refString="Schumann, K. M. (1895) Asclepiadaceae. In: Engler, H. G. A. &amp; Prantl. K. A. E. (eds.), Die Naturlichen Planzenfamilien, vol. 4, part 2. Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig, pp. 189 - 306, fig. 62 - 92." type="book chapter" year="1895">Schumann (1895)</bibRefCitation>
, respectively. The monotypic 
<taxonomicName authority="Lillo, 1919" authorityName="Lillo" authorityYear="1919" box="[716,822,423,448]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Hickenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[716,822,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Hickenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1838" authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1838" box="[1049,1160,423,448]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1049,1160,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Morrenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Goyder, D. J." box="[1205,1381,422,448]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" pagination="162" refId="ref4813" refString="Goyder, D. J. (2001) The identity of Hickenia Lillo (Apocynaceae subfam. Asclepiadoideae). Kew Bulletin 56: 162." type="journal article" year="2001">Goyder (2001)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,271,461,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Stuckertia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,271,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Stuckertia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="J.Lindley, 1838" authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1838" box="[575,688,461,486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[575,688,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Morrenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Goyder, D. J." box="[735,916,461,487]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" pagination="713 - 721" refId="ref4840" refString="Goyder, D. J. (2003) A synopsis of Morrenia Lindl. (Apocynaceae subfam. Asclepiadoideae). Kew Bulletin 58: 713 - 721." type="journal article" year="2003">Goyder (2003)</bibRefCitation>
. They are treated here within the expanded concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[292,387,500,525]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[292,387,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Araujia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on this circumscription, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[799,894,500,525]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[799,894,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Araujia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises twelve South American species occurring in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[405,524,538,564]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[644,733,538,564]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[744,854,538,564]" name="Paraguay" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, southern and south-western 
<collectingCountry box="[1193,1267,538,564]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1328,1432,538,564]" name="Uruguay" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, with a centre of diversity in the Chaco.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,152,758]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">
Below, we provide the combinations for seven of the eight species (and one subspecies) of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Goyder 2003)" authorityName="J.Lindley" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Goyder" baseAuthorityYear="2003" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1324,1435,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Morrenia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Goyder, D. J." box="[159,318,654,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" pagination="713 - 721" refId="ref4840" refString="Goyder, D. J. (2003) A synopsis of Morrenia Lindl. (Apocynaceae subfam. Asclepiadoideae). Kew Bulletin 58: 713 - 721." type="journal article" year="2003">Goyder 2003</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[365,455,655,680]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[365,455,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Araujia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="(Morong 1893: 161) Malme" authorityName="Malme" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Morong" baseAuthorityPageNumber="161" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[471,1052,654,680]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Morrenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stormiana">
<emphasis box="[471,710,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Morrenia stormiana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Morong, T. &amp; Britton, N. L." box="[727,952,654,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" pagination="45 - 280" refId="ref6019" refString="Morong, T. &amp; Britton, N. L. (1893) An enumeration of the plants collected by Dr. Thomas Morong in Paraguay, 1888 - 1890. Annals of the New York Academy of Sciences 7: 45 - 280" type="journal article" year="1893">Morong 1893: 161</bibRefCitation>
) Malme
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chodat, R. &amp; Hassler, E." box="[1091,1436,654,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" pagination="50 - 66" refId="ref4516" refString="Chodat, R. &amp; Hassler, E. (1903) Plantae Hasslerianae, soit enumeration des plants recoltees au Paraguay par le Dr Emile Hassler, d'Arau (Susisse) de 1885 a 1902, seconde partie. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, serie 2, 3: 50 - 66." type="journal article" year="1903">Chodat &amp; Hassler (1903: 65)</bibRefCitation>
was described originally under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brotero" authorityYear="1817" box="[533,625,693,718]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Araujia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[533,625,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">Araujia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We also designate 
<typeStatus box="[869,991,693,719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11">lectotypes</typeStatus>
for three species and indicate a new synonym.
</paragraph>
